5. Address research question: How predictable is March Madness?
•	March Madness is predictable in the idea that there is a higher chance in seeds 1-4 winning most of their games.
•	It becomes largely unpredictable when seeds 5-12 play, where upset rates reach ~40-50%.
•	It can be more predictable if you account for the round where the game is taking place or the seed matchup present. 
•	Conclusively, it is partially predictable because higher seeds (1-4) perform up to their standards. But there can be frequent upsets in matchups between 5-12 seeds, especially in later rounds such as the Elite Eight and the Sweet Sixteen, where overall outcomes can become extremely unpredictable.



